---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import '../styles/landing.css';

const title = 'Our Values | Appalachian Grappling Collective';
const description =
	'The values and training mentality behind Appalachian Grappling Collective.';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={title} description={description} />
	</head>
	<body class="landing-page values-page">
		<Header active="values" />

		<main>
			<section class="values-detail-section" aria-labelledby="values-detail-title">
				<div class="values-detail-panel">
					<p class="eyebrow">Our Values</p>
					<h1 id="values-detail-title">Built to strengthen more than technique.</h1>
					<div class="values-copy">
						<p>
							Appalachian Grappling Collective is built on faith, personal responsibility,
							respect, discipline, and accountability. We believe the training room should
							strengthen more than technique; it should build character, confidence, resilience,
							and trust. Every person who steps onto the mat is expected to treat others with
							dignity, control their ego, accept correction, and contribute to a safe, clean,
							and dependable training environment.
						</p> 
						<p>
							We are intentionally grassroots and selective, focused on developing a close community 
							of committed training partners rather than chasing numbers, status, or recognition. 
							Of course, if your interest is competing in BJJ tournaments or fighting competitively, 
							we certainly wouldn't discourage you! Competition is a healthy way to test your skills 
							against other experienced grapplers or fighters.
						</p>
						<p>
							At the center of our approach is a <strong>“train in truth” mentality</strong>.
							That means being honest about our skill sets, physical capabilities, weaknesses,
							and level of preparedness. We do not confuse cooperative practice with proven
							ability, and we do not promote false confidence. Our jiu-jitsu is technical,
							practical, and fight-oriented, with an emphasis on pressure, control, awareness,
							and the ability to perform when resistance is real. We train responsibly, but we
							train with purpose—seeking genuine competence, steady growth, and the confidence
							that comes from knowing our abilities have been honestly tested.
						</p>
					</div>
					<div class="values-detail-actions" aria-label="Values page actions">
						<a class="button primary" href="/apply"><span>Apply to Join!</span></a>
						<a class="button secondary dark" href="/"><span>Return Home</span></a>
					</div>
				</div>
			</section>
		</main>

		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>
